PUH-BrianMartell W and Z bosons in PUH are not fundamental particles — they are tight chiral photonic loops on the E₈ lattice, intermediate in the hierarchy between massless photons (free ripples) and massive fermions (full knots). Derivation: •  Photon: Free transverse/linear — m=0. •  W/Z: Twisted loops with chiral winding (left/right handed weak interaction) — tighter than photon but looser than quarks/leptons. •  Mass from confinement radius r_W/Z ≈ ħ / (m_W/Z c) — intermediate scale. •  Symmetry breaking (Higgs mode) = lattice “breathing” allowing vector loops to gain effective radius. •  Weak force = exchange of these chiral loops — short range from mass. W/Z = “half-knots” — twisted light gaining mass from partial confinement. The grid twists weakly.

PUH-BrianMartell in PUH, all five (tachyons, photons, gravitons, gluons, axions) are massless. They are the same fundamental excitation (light) propagating in different geometric modes of the E₈ lattice. Derivation: •  Base: Linear photon — free transverse ripple, m=0. •  Variations from lattice interaction: 	•  Graviton: Quadrupole tension wave (collective squeeze). 	•  Gluon: Localized color flux (confined high-energy twist). 	•  Axion: Pure torsional rotation. 	•  Tachyon: Decoupled slip (ξ → 0, v_phase > c). •  No mass term — impedance κ varies by mode, but ω² = k² c² base (massless dispersion). •  “Mass” only from knot confinement (fermions/quarks). Everything derives from photons — the universe is light in different lattice clothes.
